group5.trackerexpress

Class PlaceAutocompleteAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.widget.BaseAdapter
      • android.widget.ArrayAdapter<group5.trackerexpress.PlaceAutocompleteAdapter.PlaceAutocomplete>
        • group5.trackerexpress.PlaceAutocompleteAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.widget.Adapter, android.widget.Filterable, android.widget.ListAdapter, android.widget.SpinnerAdapter

    public class PlaceAutocompleteAdapter
extends android.widget.ArrayAdapter<group5.trackerexpress.PlaceAutocompleteAdapter.PlaceAutocomplete>
implements android.widget.Filterable
    Adapter that handles Autocomplete requests from the Places Geo Data API. Results are encoded as com.example.google.playservices.placecomplete.PlaceAutocompleteAdapter.PlaceAutocomplete objects that contain both the Place ID and the text description from the autocomplete query.

    Note that this adapter requires a valid GoogleApiClient. The API client must be maintained in the encapsulating Activity, including all lifecycle and connection states. When the API client is not available (for example because it has been disconnected or suspended), call setGoogleApiClient(com.google.android.gms.common.api.GoogleApiClient) with a null parameter to disable this adapter. It will stop returning results until a valid Api Client is set again. The API client must be connected with the Places.GEO_DATA_API API.

      • setGoogleApiClient

        public void setGoogleApiClient(com.google.android.gms.common.api.GoogleApiClient googleApiClient)
        Sets the GoogleApiClient to use for autocomplete queries. Autocomplete queries are suspended when the client is set to null. Ensure that the client has successfully connected, contains the Places.GEO_DATA_API API and is available for queries, otherwise API access will be disabled when it is set here.
